article.headline: Northern Arizona defeats UC Davis 21-10
article.story: DAVIS, Calif. -- Lucky Dozier lived up to his name, as his 78-yard interception return for a touchdown helped Northern Arizona to a 21-10 win over UC Davis. With 1:56 left, Marcus Alford sealed the win for Northern Arizona (1-1) with a 47-yard interception return to provide the final margin. Zach Bauman became the Aggies' all-time leading rusher with 3,803 yards, breaking Marcus King's school record of 3,794 set in 2001. Bauman finished with 56 yards on 18 carries. UC Davis (0-3) held a 10-7 lead entering the fourth quarter based on Jimmy Laughrea's 23-yard touchdown run and Brady Stuart's 25-yard field goal. Northern Arizona had the last laugh though, as Laughrea tossed the two costly fourth-quarter picks. Laughrea finished 16 of 33 for 154 yards. Though both teams play in the Big Sky Conference, the result will not count against their conference record.
